}minus;1.0{\&}thinsp;{\%} (Arctic) and {\&}minus;0.3{\&}thinsp;{\%} to {\&}minus;1.1{\&}thinsp;{\%} (Antarctic). Products of group II appear to be mostly biased high in the Arctic by between +1.0{\&}thinsp;{\%} and +3.5{\&}thinsp;{\%}, while their biases in the Antarctic only range from {\&}minus;0.2{\&}thinsp; to +0.9{\&}thinsp;{\%}. The standard deviation is smaller in the Arctic for the quoted group I products: 1.9{\&}thinsp;{\%} to 2.9{\&}thinsp;{\%} and Antarctic: 2.5{\&}thinsp;{\%} to 3.1{\&}thinsp;{\%}, than for group II products: Arctic: 3.6{\&}thinsp;{\%} to 5.0{\&}thinsp;{\%}, Antarctic: 4.5{\&}thinsp;{\%} to 5.4{\&}thi{\ldots}},
